        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 9:31PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 931 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 18
miles northeast of Garrison, or 22 miles west of Helena, moving north
at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lincoln, Wolf Creek, Marysville, Tower Rock State Park, Craig, Canyon
Creek, Austin, and Bean Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
